//============================================================ Increment & Decrement Programs ============================================================//

ðŸ’»Program 1:
int a = 5;
int b = a++;
System.out.println("a: " + a + ", b: " + b);

ðŸ§ Logic:
Before the operation:
a = 5
Assign to b: The value of a (which is 5) is assigned to b.
So now: b = 5
Increment a: After assigning the value to b, a is incremented by 1.
Now: a = 6

Answer: a: 6, b: 5

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ðŸ’»Program 2:
int i = 1;
i = i++ + ++i;
System.out.println(i); // ?

ðŸ§ Logic:
i = 1 + 3

Answer: i = 4

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ðŸ’»Program 3:
int x = 5;
System.out.println(x++ + ++x); // ?
x = 5 + 7

Answer: x = 12

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ðŸ’»Program 4:
int x = 5;
System.out.println(++x); // Output: ?
System.out.println(x++); // Output: ?
System.out.println(x); // Output: ?

ðŸ§ Logic:
++x: 6 (pre increment. So, 5+1)
x++: 6 (post increment. So, 6)
x: 7 (x = 6 after post increment became x = 6+1 = 7)

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ðŸ’»Program 5: Interview Question
int a = 5;
int b = a++ + ++a;
System.out.println("a: " + a); // Output: ?
System.out.println("b: " + b); // Output: ?

ðŸ§ Logic:
a = 5 + 1 + 1 = 7
b = 5 + 7

Answer:
b: 5 + 7 = 12
a: 7

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ðŸ’»Program 6: Interview Question
int x = 5;
int y = x++ + ++x + x++ + ++x;
System.out.println("x = " + x + ", y = " + y);

ðŸ§ Logic:
X = 9
Y = 5 + 7 + 7 + 9 = 28

